DESCRIPTION PHYSIQUE: "Red mud is mostly made up of fine elements, clays and silts (the fraction <5µm is approximately 60%). The chemical analysis indicates the following average values: • Water content: between 40 and 46% • Iron oxide (in the form of clay particles): 45% (in % DM) • Sodium silico-aluminate (in the form of crystals cementing the iron oxide particles): 37% (in % DM) • Titanate of Calcium (in crystalline form): 10% (in % DM) These three compounds therefore represent 92% of the dry matter. Among the other constituents are complex compounds of Manganese, Phosphorus, Vanadium, Fluorine, Chromium, etc. (2,000,000 t)"
